org.apache.river.qa.harness

Class TestList

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.qa.harness.TestList

  • public class TestList
extends Object
    A data structure that holds the test to run, rerun, and their results. This object relies on these config entries:
    • org.apache.river.qa.harness.rerunFailedTests is a boolean flag that controls whether or not failed tests should be rerun
    • org.apache.river.qa.harness.testMaxRetries specifies the maximum number of times to rerun a single failing test

        public void add(TestRun run)
         throws IllegalArgumentException
        Add the given TestRun to the list of test to run if it is not already in the test list. Duplicate TestRun objects are NOT allowed.
        Parameters:
        run - the TestRun object to add
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - the run object has already been added

      • hasMore

        public boolean hasMore()
        Represents the check for more elements in the iteration over the test list. Elements added after the iteration has started will still be included in the iteration. Test list may only be iterated over once.

      • next

        public TestRun next()
             throws NoSuchElementException
        Represents an iterator over the elements of the test list. If a returned TestRun object represents a rerun, then the isRerun field of the TestRun is set to true; false otherwise. Elements added after the iteration has started will still be included in the iteration. Test list may only be iterated over once.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - no more elements in the list
